in letting us turn apps on and off without uninstalling them. You can leave Social Say.So installed, and only activate it when you need it, or want to take advantage of a Social Say.So offer, then deactivate it after you''re done. No more uninstalling and reinstalling! <a href=\"http://bit.ly/U2Wqyc\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> for further instructions on how to disable this app.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>How do I remove the Social Say.So browser extension?</strong><br />\n	If you want to remove the app from your browser, here are instructions for each major browser type.  If you decide later to reinstall, use your original registration email and your PaySos, level progress and earning will be there where you left off! For removal instructions\n	<a href=\"http://bit.ly/V3ht4y\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>How do I link my Facebook or Twitter account?</strong><br />\n	You can check <a href=\"http://bit.ly/V6wRNX\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a> for instructions on how to link your Facebook / Twitter account, or see below.\n</p>\n<ol>\n	<li>Click \"Edit Profile\"</li>\n	<li>Click to link your Twitter or Facebook account.</li>\n	<li>Allow access in order for the accounts to be linked.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n	<strong>How do I disconnect my Facebook / Twitter account from the Say.So bar?</strong><br />\n	You can check <a href=\"http://bit.ly/Y62izt\" target=\"_blank\">HERE</a> for instructions on how to unlink your Facebook / Twitter account, or see below.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Facebook:</strong><br />\n</p>\n<ol>\n	<li>Log into Facebook.</li>\n	<li>Click on <em>Home</em> > <em>Account Settings.</em></li>\n	<li>Click on <em>Apps</em>. You will see <em>Say.So app</em> listed here.</li>\n	<li>Click on the app and then <em>Remove App</em> in the top right area of the application info box.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n	<strong>Twitter:</strong><br />\n</p>\n<ol>\n	<li>Log into Twitter.</li>\n	<li>Click on your profile icon (top right part of your screen) > <em>Settings</em>.</li>\n	<li>Open the <em>Applications</em> tab and you will see the <em>Say.So app</em> listed here.</li>\n	<li>Click on <em>Revoke Access</em> to remove the app.</li>\n</ol>\n<br /><br />\n'),
